26/09/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- The justice ministers of Croatia, Serbia-Montenegro, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Macedonia, Bulgaria, Romania and Albania agreed on Friday (24 September) to adopt a joint strategy against organised crime. 
They also decided to establish a system for exchanging information between respective police forces and judiciaries. 
"One country cannot fight alone against crime and the mafia. 
It is necessary to find ways and join efforts to respond in an effective way to aggression ... 
of criminal organisations," Albanian President Alfred Moisiu told the ministers. 
Extraditions and standards of prisoner treatment were also discussed. 
(Albanian News, Anadolu Agency - 25/09/04; AFP - 24/09/04)
